My intention here was not so much to criticize 
@coindesk
 but to point out that, as opposed to the Bitcoin consensus layer, people can freely experiment with LN and even deploy variants with different limits...without seriously affecting anyone else.

 ¬∑ Mar 14, 2019
One of the nicest things about LN is that it does not touch the Bitcoin consensus layer, so different ideas can be tried out (even ideas that compete with LN) without requiring any forks with high risk of a chain split.

Don't like it? Get creative!
